250
00:14:27,860 --> 00:14:28,900
(Jungang Real Estate Agency)

251
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:31,429
The moms are way ahead of you.

252
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:34,470
We're out of long-term
and short-term rentals.

253
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:37,610
What's available is more expensive
than it was a month ago.

254
00:14:37,809 --> 00:14:41,610
Your budget will only get you a studio
or two rooms in a semi-basement,

255
00:14:41,740 --> 00:14:45,010
but you'd be lucky
to find one that's available now.

256
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:47,120
What should we do?

257
00:14:49,279 --> 00:14:51,590
My hair's standing on end.

258
00:14:52,220 --> 00:14:53,890
What if it falls out?

259
00:14:55,020 --> 00:14:56,029
Oh, dear.

260
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:58,529
I talked Mom into selling the house.

261
00:14:59,730 --> 00:15:01,429
What if she finds out?

262
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,000
Goodness.

263
00:15:07,299 --> 00:15:08,340
It's Mom.

264
00:15:15,110 --> 00:15:16,679
Hi, Mom.

265
00:15:16,679 --> 00:15:19,309
Hey! All of you, get over here now!

266
00:15:25,789 --> 00:15:28,990
What does this say? What is this about?

267
00:15:32,029 --> 00:15:35,400
Our neighbors are celebrating.

268
00:15:35,559 --> 00:15:37,199
What will happen to us?

269
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:39,069
- Mom...
- Forget it.

270
00:15:39,199 --> 00:15:41,340
I'm sad we couldn't get more
for the house,

271
00:15:41,370 --> 00:15:43,939
but can we move into the place
you said you'd found?

272
00:15:43,939 --> 00:15:46,840
The school nearby is going to become...

273
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:48,809
some fancy global school.

274
00:15:49,279 --> 00:15:50,949
It's popular with the students now.

275
00:15:51,010 --> 00:15:53,679
- So what?
- The price to rent went up.

276
00:15:54,579 --> 00:15:57,150
You said the housing price here
would never go up.

277
00:15:57,220 --> 00:15:59,390
It hasn't been that long
since we sold the house.

278
00:15:59,459 --> 00:16:02,559
The ink on the contract
we signed is barely dry.

279
00:16:02,559 --> 00:16:05,789
It would smudge if I were
to run my finger over the seal.

280
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:07,860
Say something!

281
00:16:07,860 --> 00:16:10,600
The prices hadn't gone up in years.

282
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:13,100
Even when the prices elsewhere went up,

283
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:15,900
- it even went down here, right?
- Darn you.

284
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:18,970
Not even experts can predict
how housing prices...

285
00:16:18,970 --> 00:16:20,610
You!

286
00:16:21,079 --> 00:16:22,949
- Oh, dear.
- Mom!

287
00:16:23,510 --> 00:16:25,980
If not even experts know,

288
00:16:26,220 --> 00:16:29,150
why did you act like you knew something?

289
00:16:29,179 --> 00:16:31,250
The population's dwindling...

290
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:33,890
and houses are being built, so what?

291
00:16:33,919 --> 00:16:37,329
- I thought...
- You two! You're both frauds!

292
00:16:37,459 --> 00:16:39,959
You're the worst accomplice ever!

293
00:16:40,130 --> 00:16:43,600
What now? Oh, dear. What happens now?

294
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:47,039
Jin Ju, go and close the salon.

295
00:16:47,039 --> 00:16:48,770
I can't work today.

296
00:16:48,770 --> 00:16:51,140
Oh, dear. I need some rest.

297
00:16:51,270 --> 00:16:53,579
Oh, my gosh...

298
00:16:57,079 --> 00:16:59,380
I'm home...

299
00:17:02,079 --> 00:17:03,150
What's this?

300
00:17:05,419 --> 00:17:06,720
This place is getting redeveloped?

301
00:17:08,760 --> 00:17:12,959
I did say we shouldn't sell the house.

302
00:17:12,959 --> 00:17:14,800
You be quiet.

303
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:18,729
This wouldn't have happened
if you hadn't gotten into trouble.

304
00:17:18,969 --> 00:17:21,969
If we're talking about who's guilty,
most of it falls on you.

305
00:17:23,939 --> 00:17:26,209
It's so darn annoying.

306
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:28,439
How could this happen now?

307
00:17:28,439 --> 00:17:31,009
The speculator scored big
by buying our house,

308
00:17:31,009 --> 00:17:34,320
and we stupidly gave him
a 5,000-dollar discount.

309
00:17:36,590 --> 00:17:38,390
Jin Ju. Give me his number.

310
00:17:39,350 --> 00:17:40,390
Okay.

311
00:18:01,179 --> 00:18:03,080
I'm going to call So Woo...

312
00:18:04,110 --> 00:18:06,519
- to the office tomorrow.
- What for?

313
00:18:06,679 --> 00:18:09,749
You and Jeon are to face him
in my presence.

314
00:18:10,050 --> 00:18:11,320
You both can get on your knees.

315
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:14,159
What if word were to spread
within the company?

316
00:18:14,159 --> 00:18:17,229
Who wouldn't know by now
when the video was everywhere?

317
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:20,530
You shouldn't have done that
if you didn't want to be embarrassed.

318
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:29,300
Darn it.

319
00:18:33,709 --> 00:18:35,479
Hey, Woo Sang.

320
00:18:35,479 --> 00:18:37,479
- Look at this.
- Darn it, Mom.

321
00:18:37,709 --> 00:18:39,150
Can you stop doing that?

322
00:18:39,150 --> 00:18:41,219
I won't look. You look at this.

323
00:18:41,219 --> 00:18:42,519
Come here.

324
00:18:42,949 --> 00:18:45,090
- Look.
- Do what you want...

325
00:18:45,090 --> 00:18:46,489
- if you want another lawsuit!
- What's this?

326
00:18:46,489 --> 00:18:47,919
It's Sang Ah.

327
00:18:48,219 --> 00:18:51,330
I was there when it happened and I saw...

328
00:18:51,429 --> 00:18:54,729
No. I didn't see it,
but I heard everything.

329
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,800
Sang Ah had an affair.
Do you believe that?

330
00:18:59,199 --> 00:19:01,300
- Why did she do that?
- I don't know.

331
00:19:01,570 --> 00:19:04,769
The fraudster family came by
and threw cash in the air...

332
00:19:04,769 --> 00:19:06,280
and there was a huge ruckus.

333
00:19:07,179 --> 00:19:09,280
She had the affair
with someone from that family.

334
00:19:10,249 --> 00:19:11,979
- From that family?
- Yes.

335
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:14,979
That family scares me too.

336
00:19:15,979 --> 00:19:17,689
They're messed up as well.

337
00:19:18,890 --> 00:19:20,320
Should I switch salons?

338
00:19:21,159 --> 00:19:24,830
Will they refund
what's left of my membership?

339
00:19:25,989 --> 00:19:27,130
Will they?

340
00:19:30,769 --> 00:19:32,199
What will you say?

341
00:19:32,199 --> 00:19:33,499
I'm annoyed.

342
00:19:33,499 --> 00:19:35,370
I'll ask him to go back on the deal.

343
00:19:35,370 --> 00:19:36,840
Would you do that if you were him?

344
00:19:36,840 --> 00:19:39,209
We took half the going price
and paid the settlement.

345
00:19:39,780 --> 00:19:43,110
We can't cough up the money
even if he agrees to annul the deal.

346
00:19:43,110 --> 00:19:46,449
Then I'll get him to hand over
the extra 5,000 dollars.

347
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:48,850
The person is unable to answer the phone.

348
00:19:48,850 --> 00:19:50,590
Why won't he pick up?

349
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:57,590
What could be wrong?

350
00:19:58,459 --> 00:19:59,900
- Dad.
- Yes?

351
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:01,300
Why can't we catch anything?

352
00:20:02,429 --> 00:20:03,499
I don't know.

353
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:07,699
Are the fish hiding because it's too cold?

354
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:12,370
Come on out, fish.

355
00:20:12,370 --> 00:20:14,709
Come on out, fish.

356
00:20:17,449 --> 00:20:18,880
It's not usually this bad.

357
00:20:19,509 --> 00:20:20,550
What's wrong?

358
00:20:22,219 --> 00:20:25,719
Do you think he saved your number
to avoid picking up?

359
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:28,060
I'll try calling from my phone.

360
00:20:28,519 --> 00:20:30,489
What will you say?

361
00:20:30,489 --> 00:20:33,600
I'd rather say something
than shut up and do nothing.

362
00:20:34,759 --> 00:20:36,769
We have nothing more to lose.

363
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:42,570
What could be the matter?

364
00:20:43,209 --> 00:20:44,509
I'm not this bad at fishing.

365
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:46,040
Goodness.

366
00:20:48,380 --> 00:20:49,409
Oh, well.

367
00:20:50,380 --> 00:20:52,310
Wait here for a bit, Tae Ri.

368
00:20:52,310 --> 00:20:53,350
Okay.

369
00:21:04,989 --> 00:21:05,989
Hello?

370
00:21:05,989 --> 00:21:08,560
Hello. Are you...

371
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,100
Are you Mr. Kim So Woo?

372
00:21:11,300 --> 00:21:12,699
Yes. Who's this?

373
00:21:12,699 --> 00:21:15,739
You bought the house in Manjang-dong.

374
00:21:15,969 --> 00:21:18,909
We talked yesterday on my sister's phone.

375
00:21:18,909 --> 00:21:22,979
Oh. I already told you
you can't keep the salon.

376
00:21:22,979 --> 00:21:25,050
No, it's not about that.

377
00:21:25,509 --> 00:21:27,050
Can we meet for a chat?

378
00:21:28,419 --> 00:21:29,479
What for?

379
00:21:29,479 --> 00:21:32,390
There's a really important issue.

380
00:21:32,749 --> 00:21:36,019
You could come over
or we could meet in the middle.

381
00:21:36,019 --> 00:21:39,060
I'm not in Seoul,
so I don't think we can meet.

382
00:21:39,060 --> 00:21:41,499
I'll come to you, then.

383
00:21:42,030 --> 00:21:43,229
It's too late today.

384
00:21:43,229 --> 00:21:46,870
I'll leave early tomorrow morning
and call when I'm nearby.

385
00:21:47,870 --> 00:21:49,040
Hello?

386
00:21:49,739 --> 00:21:50,769
Hello?

387
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:56,009
Will he see you?

388
00:21:58,280 --> 00:22:00,249
How big is his family?

389
00:22:00,419 --> 00:22:02,919
He came to see the house with his son.

390
00:22:03,650 --> 00:22:07,189
I got the impression he was alone.
Like a single dad raising his kid?

391
00:22:07,659 --> 00:22:10,330
He looked like real easy prey.

392
00:22:10,330 --> 00:22:12,060
He didn't look like a speculator.

393
00:22:13,030 --> 00:22:15,100
Speculators don't go around with a sign.

394
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:18,769
Naive-looking people are the worst.

395
00:22:21,469 --> 00:22:23,840
(Han Hair Line)

396
00:22:24,570 --> 00:22:26,110
Hello. I'm here.

397
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:30,280
I said I'd come, so here I am.

398
00:22:31,479 --> 00:22:34,580
Yes. I turned left from the sign.

399
00:22:36,249 --> 00:22:37,519
Okay.

400
00:22:40,860 --> 00:22:42,360
- Was that good?
- Yes.

401
00:22:43,759 --> 00:22:47,300
Someone's here.
I'll go and chat with them.

402
00:22:47,499 --> 00:22:48,530
Okay.

403
00:22:57,110 --> 00:22:59,640
- Oh, hello.
- Hello.

404
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:03,949
Are you out camping with your son?

405
00:23:04,479 --> 00:23:05,550
Yes.

406
00:23:07,850 --> 00:23:08,880
Have fun.

407
00:23:10,949 --> 00:23:13,419
I'm here on an errand.

408
00:23:13,419 --> 00:23:14,489
I see.

409
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:29,140
Hello?

410
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,239
It's me.

411
00:23:35,409 --> 00:23:36,439
You...

412
00:23:42,050 --> 00:23:43,390
I think it's me.

413
00:23:49,719 --> 00:23:52,659
You bought the house?

414
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:56,499
Weren't you a jobless dad?

415
00:23:56,729 --> 00:23:58,330
I had some savings.

416
00:23:59,699 --> 00:24:00,939
That's good to hear.

417
00:24:02,140 --> 00:24:04,340
I really should worry less about others.

418
00:24:04,769 --> 00:24:07,140
I thought you were penniless and jobless.

419
00:24:10,709 --> 00:24:13,519
You got a really good deal on the house.

420
00:24:14,749 --> 00:24:17,519
Yes. Why did you want to see me?

421
00:24:18,090 --> 00:24:20,019
Oh, that.

422
00:24:21,790 --> 00:24:22,790
Well...

423
00:24:25,630 --> 00:24:30,300
Did you buy our house because
you heard the area would be redeveloped?

424
00:24:31,229 --> 00:24:33,269
- What?
- Did you hear rumors...

425
00:24:33,269 --> 00:24:34,600
and decide to make a profit?

426
00:24:34,669 --> 00:24:35,870
No way.

427
00:24:37,269 --> 00:24:38,409
I did not.

428
00:24:39,169 --> 00:24:42,840
How did you decide to buy
at just the right time?

429
00:24:43,110 --> 00:24:45,449
The area's not that well-known.

430
00:24:45,509 --> 00:24:47,449
Did you get the feel...

431
00:24:47,449 --> 00:24:49,679
to buy a house there
right before the huge announcement?

432
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:51,219
If that were the case,

433
00:24:52,090 --> 00:24:53,620
will you report me to someone?

434
00:24:54,290 --> 00:24:55,290
Goodness.

435
00:24:56,519 --> 00:24:58,390
No, I wouldn't do that.

436
00:24:58,390 --> 00:25:01,600
Do you want me to go back on the deal?

437
00:25:02,860 --> 00:25:04,030
Well...

438
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:09,439
Could you give us one year?

439
00:25:10,969 --> 00:25:13,840
It would be even better
if you could give us two years.

440
00:25:14,679 --> 00:25:17,350
Can you let us stay there
while we pay you back?

441
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:21,019
No.

442
00:25:23,249 --> 00:25:26,620
If you didn't speculate,
you didn't know the price would go up.

443
00:25:27,489 --> 00:25:30,229
Will you let us sign
a long-term lease with you...

444
00:25:30,390 --> 00:25:32,659
at the price we agreed on?

445
00:25:35,159 --> 00:25:36,360
I can't do that.

446
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:41,870
I'm not asking you to annul the deal.

447
00:25:41,870 --> 00:25:44,870
You must be pleased to make a profit.
It'll be just two years.

448
00:25:45,370 --> 00:25:47,009
We'll keep the house clean.

449
00:25:48,979 --> 00:25:52,679
I promise to... Please. Mr. Kim.

450
00:25:52,979 --> 00:25:55,519
You know I'm an interior designer.

451
00:25:55,519 --> 00:25:59,150
I'll fix up the house while we live there.

452
00:25:59,850 --> 00:26:01,790
Why are you chasing me?

453
00:26:01,959 --> 00:26:04,459
I heard you were in urgent need of money,

454
00:26:04,890 --> 00:26:08,130
so I paid you half the going price
which you'd usually get a few weeks later.

455
00:26:08,929 --> 00:26:10,800
I know that.

456
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:14,070
You're rich enough
to be able to afford paying us...

457
00:26:14,070 --> 00:26:15,540
half the price in one go.

458
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:18,509
You must be living somewhere right now.

459
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:21,909
That's called speculation!

460
00:26:22,310 --> 00:26:24,909
I'm not living anywhere right now.

461
00:26:25,179 --> 00:26:27,479
I'm out camping, as you can see.

462
00:26:29,380 --> 00:26:30,989
I closed all my savings accounts...

463
00:26:31,189 --> 00:26:33,249
to buy a house to live in with my son.

464
00:26:33,459 --> 00:26:34,719
How is that speculation?

465
00:26:38,030 --> 00:26:39,060
Wait.

466
00:26:41,699 --> 00:26:43,530
If you'll move in with your son...

467
00:26:45,630 --> 00:26:48,469
You didn't reconcile with your wife?

468
00:26:50,209 --> 00:26:51,209
No.

469
00:26:57,709 --> 00:27:00,850
I'm really sorry you didn't.

470
00:27:03,689 --> 00:27:06,320
That house is too big
for one adult and one kid.

471
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:08,360
Why do you need four rooms?

472
00:27:08,459 --> 00:27:11,390
Let my family stay there
on a long-term lease...

473
00:27:11,390 --> 00:27:14,100
and move into
a clean two-room apartment with...

474
00:27:14,100 --> 00:27:16,560
No, thanks. That's enough.

475
00:27:17,429 --> 00:27:18,499
Wait.

476
00:27:21,400 --> 00:27:23,969
I'm really sorry but...

477
00:27:24,709 --> 00:27:26,669
my mom's salon at least...

478
00:27:28,880 --> 00:27:30,909
I plan to turn that space into my office.

479
00:27:31,080 --> 00:27:32,949
What jobless guy needs an office?

480
00:27:34,219 --> 00:27:35,679
Shouldn't you look for work?

481
00:27:36,019 --> 00:27:38,519
I'd like to make an office
because I need one.

482
00:27:38,890 --> 00:27:40,860
I chose that house
because it would be easier...

483
00:27:40,860 --> 00:27:43,429
to raise my son
if my office and home were adjoined.

484
00:27:44,060 --> 00:27:46,689
I don't even know
why I'm explaining this to you.

485
00:27:46,689 --> 00:27:48,600
What I decide to do...

486
00:27:49,999 --> 00:27:51,570
with the leftover rooms is up to me.

487
00:27:53,100 --> 00:27:54,239
Goodbye.

488
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,919
(Desperate Mrs. Seon Ju)

489
00:28:28,199 --> 00:28:29,840
(Desperate Mrs. Seon Ju)

490
00:28:29,840 --> 00:28:31,070
You didn't drive here?

491
00:28:31,070 --> 00:28:33,610
My car exploded, so I scrapped it.

492
00:28:33,610 --> 00:28:34,679
It exploded?

493
00:28:34,679 --> 00:28:38,310
Come on. You made me
sign a contract so I wouldn't tell.

494
00:28:38,310 --> 00:28:39,880
My watch is missing.

495
00:28:40,050 --> 00:28:41,479
I want to see what's in all your bags.

496
00:28:41,479 --> 00:28:43,620
How dare you let
a video like that get out?

497
00:28:43,949 --> 00:28:45,689
Did we kill someone?

498
00:28:45,689 --> 00:28:47,259
How far are you going to go?

499
00:28:47,259 --> 00:28:49,189
I might as well marry Mr. Jeon.

500
00:28:50,159 --> 00:28:52,159
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
